│ re-evaluated. It retains its initial `true` value, leading the compiler to believe all     │
│ incoming GEPs were `inbounds` when they were not.                                          │
│                                                                                            │
│ In this specific case, the initial GEPs have a `i32` element type, but the outer GEP has   │
│ an `i8` element type (after an earlier transformation). This type mismatch causes the      │
│ check for "all incoming values are GEPs with the same base pointer and compatible types"   │
│ to fail, the loop is skipped, and the `AllSameInbounds` flag incorrectly remains `true`.   │
│                                                                                            │
│ The fix is to initialize `AllSameInbounds` to `false` before this check. If the check then │
│ succeeds and we find that all incoming GEPs are indeed `inbounds`, we can then set it to   │
│ `true`. This ensures the flag is only `true` when we have explicitly proven it to be so.   │
